@NODE Warum "Why MultiIndicator"

@{b}@{u}Why MultiIndicator ?@{uu}@{ub}


Read the following features and @{u}compare@{uu} with other programs !


@{b}1.@{ub}  MultiIndicator shows ASC-files (with or without ESC-sequences and Tabs),
    HEX-files and Guide-files (if a external Guideindicator is available).
    MultiIndicator dicides automatically if it uses the ASC-, HEX- or Guide-
    indicator.

@{b}2.@{ub}  MultiIndicator passes over ESC-sequences which would impair the output
    on the screen.

@{b}3.@{ub}  MultiIndicator can konfigure with the Prefs-file, the Shellparamters or
    the ToolTypes, that means you can always konfigure MultiIndicator
    differencly.

@{b}4.@{ub}  MultiIndicator opens an AppIcon, if it was started from the Workbench,
    so you can use it when you need it.

@{b}5.@{ub}  MultiIndicator shows compressed Guidefiles exactly. This is not possible
    if you use @{"Amigaguide" link Lizenz} or Multiview alone.

@{b}6.@{ub}  You can compress and crypt files with XPK. MultiIndicator realizes if
    a file is compressed and crypted, for example you can compress a file
    with SHRI and than crypt that file with FEAL - MultiIndicator realizes
    this.

@{b}7.@{ub}  MultiIndicator has a comfortable printoption, so you needn't an specially
    printutility for ASC-files.

@{b}8.@{ub}  MultiIndicator supports the localization under Workbench 2.1.

@{b}9.@{ub}  MultiIndicator supports many options of OS 3.0, for example scaleable
    Gadgets, NewLookMenues, Waitpointer and other.

@{b}10.@{ub} MultiIndicator has a very good help.


These are only the most important features.

@ENDNODE

@NODE MultiTool "MultiTool II"

@{b}@{u}Information about MultiTool II@{uu}@{ub}


MultiTool II is a great Dos-Utility. You can get this program about Amiga-
Net-Server or FD-dealer (for example Time-series and SaarAG-series).

MultiTool II was coded by

                       @{b}Boris Jakubaschk@{ub}
                       Neue Straße 14/1
                       70186 Stuttgart
                       Germany

                       E-Mail:
                       Boris@alice.tynet.sub.org


The entries for MultiIndicator in the MTool.Prefs-file are:

???? <Path>/MI "%s" @{"[parameters]" link Shell}
ASC  <Path>/MI "%s" @{"[parameters]" link Shell}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Hardware "Hardware Requirements"

@{b}@{u}Hardware Requirements for MultiIndicator@{uu}@{ub}


You need an Amiga with 512 KByte (@{u}better 1 MByte or more@{uu}), at least OS 2.0
and two disk drives or a harddisk.

MultiIndicator was coded on an Amiga 4000-040 with OS 3.0 and tested on an
Amiga 500+ with 1 MByte memory, OS 2.0 and two disk drives.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "Installation"

@{b}@{u}Install MultiIndicator@{uu}@{ub}


Use the Install-Script to install MultiIndicator.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Starten "Start MultiIndicator"

@{b}@{u}Start MultiIndicator@{uu}@{ub}


MultiIndicator either can start about Workbench or from Shell.


          @{b}Workbench@{ub}

            @{"about Icon" link Icon}
            @{"as DefaultTool" link DefTool}


          @{"Shell" link Shell}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Icon "Icon"

@{b}@{u}Start about Workbench with Icon@{uu}@{ub}


For starting MultiIndicator about Icon, you have to click the Icon twice.
The program reads the settings from the ToolTypes and the MI.Prefs-file,
wich the ToolTypes have priority.
MultiIndicator creates an AppIcon after it was started. If you click this
AppIcon twice, than an ASL-Filerequester appears and you can select the
file. If you drag and drop another Icon on the AppIcon, than the file to
this Icon will be indicated immediately.

@{u}ToolTypes:@{uu}

If you want to change the ToolTypes, click the MultiIndicatoricon and select
the menuitem Information. Now change the ToolTypes and save it.

  @{b}Pubscreen=@{ub}Screen where the window should be opened

  @{b}Guideindicator=@{ub}Indicator for Guide-files

  @{b}Gadgetfontname=@{ub}Gadgetfontname

  @{b}Gadgetfontheight=@{ub}Gadgetfontheight

  @{b}Textfontname=@{ub}Textfontname

  @{b}Textfontheight=@{ub}Textfontheight

  @{b}ESC-Tabs=@{ub}YES or NO

  @{b}FormFeed=@{ub}YES or NO

  @{b}IconX=@{ub}X-position of AppIcon

  @{b}IconY=@{ub}Y-position of AppIcon

@ENDNODE

@NODE DefTool "DefaultTool"

@{b}@{u}Start as DefaultTool@{uu}@{ub}


If you want to use MultiIndicator as DefaultTool, than the program which
should be indicated must have a ProjectIcon. Click this ProjectIcon and
select the menuitem Information. The Iconwindow appears including the
Default Tool line in which you enter MI with complete path.


If the file MIndicator.Prefs exists the fonts, screen, guideindicator and
so on were loaded from this file. If MIndicator.Prefs doesn't exist, the
internal settings were used.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Shell "Shell"

@{b}@{u}Start from Shell@{uu}@{ub}


If you start MultiIndicator from the Shell, the parameters replace the
settings in the MIndicator.Prefs.


Syntax:


MI <@{b}File@{ub}>  @{b}-PUB@{ub} [Pubscreen]
           @{b}-GUI@{ub} [Guideindicator]
           @{b}-GFO@{ub} [Gadgetfont] [Gadgetfontheight]
           @{b}-TFO@{ub} [Textfont] [Textfontheight]
           @{b}-ESC@{ub} (YES/NO)
           @{b}-FOR@{ub} (YES/NO)
           @{b}-NOP@{ub} {No Preferences}
           @{b}?@{ub} {This Line}


 @{b}Datei@{ub}      Name of the indicating File

 @{b}-PUB@{ub}       Name of the screen where the MultiIndicatorwindow appears.
            For example enter -PUB MTOOLSCREEN for the program @{"Multi-" link MultiTool}
            @{"Tool II" link MultiTool},if it was started on an own screen.
            @{i}Internal: Workbench@{ui}

 @{b}-GUI@{ub}       Here you can select the GuideIndicator which was used, if the
            indicating file is a Guidefile. Is no GuideIndicator available,
            the Guidefile will be shown as a normal ASC-file.
            @{i}Internal: SYS:Utilities/@{"AmigaGuide" link Lizenz}@{ui}

 @{b}-GFO@{ub}       Name and height of the font which was used for the text.
            For example -GFO Beispiel.font 11
            @{i}Internal: Topaz.font 8@{ui}

 @{b}-TFO@{ub}       Name and height of the font which was used for the gadgets.
            For example -TFO Beispiel.font 11
            @{i}Internal: Topaz.font 8@{ui}

 @{b}-ESC@{ub}       You can select between ESC- or ASC-description.
            @{i}Internal: YES@{ui}

 @{b}-FOR@{ub}       You can select, if a formfeed is necessery or not.
            @{i}Internal: YES@{ui}

 @{b}-NOP@{ub}       The settingsfile MIndicator.Prefs wouldn't load.

 @{b}?@{ub}          Shows syntax.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Hilfe "Help"

@{b}@{u}The Help from MultiIndicator@{ub}@{uu}


Place the Pointer about a menuitem or a gadget and press the helpbutton.


The file Mi.help must available in the directory S: or ENV:. This does the
Installer automatically.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Menüs "Menues"

@{b}@{u}The Menues from MultiIndicator@{ub}@{uu}


MultiIndicator containes following menuitems:

          @{b}Projekt@{ub}

            @{"Open... O" link Öffnen}
            @{"About A" link Über}
            @{"Info N" link Info}
            @{"Quit Q" link Ende}


          @{b}Preferences@{ub}

            @{"Save to S:" link StS}
            @{"Save to ENV:" link StENV}
            @{b}The next menuitem is only available in ASC-mode !@{ub}
            @{"ESC-Tabs E" link ESC}
            @{"Publicscreen... P" link Pub}
            @{"Guideindicator... I" link GUI}
            @{"Textfont... T" link TFo}
            @{"Gadgetfont... G" link GFo}


          @{b}The next whole menuitem is only available in ASC-mode !@{ub}

          @{b}Printer@{ub}

            @{"FormFeed F" link FOR}
            @{"Print... R" link PRT}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Öffnen "Menuitem Open..."

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem Open...@{uu}@{ub}


Opens an ASL-Filerequester in which you can select a new file.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Über "Menuitem About"

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem About@{uu}@{ub}


Opens a window which shows the name of the program, version and programer.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Info "Menuitem Info"

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem Info@{uu}@{ub}


Opens a window which gives informations about the loaded file, how packer
was used ( if file compressed with XPK or PowerPacker ), the packed length,
the unpacked length, the ratio and information about the chipmemory and
fastmemory.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Ende "Menuitem Quit"

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem Quit@{uu}@{ub}


If MIndicator was started about Shell or as DefTool, than MIndicator termi-
nated. If MIndicator was started about Workbench, than the quitwindow
appears which ask you if you want to only close only the MIndicatorwindow
or if you want to terminate the program.

@ENDNODE

@NODE StS "Menuitem Save to S:"

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem Save to S:@{uu}@{ub}


The preferencefile MIndicator.Prefs will be saved in the directory S: on the
bootdisk or on the bootpartition of the harddisk.

@ENDNODE

@NODE StENV "Menuitem Save to ENV:"

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem Save to ENV:@{uu}@{ub}


The preferencefile MIndicator.Prefs will be saved in the directory ENVARC:
and ENV:.

@ENDNODE

@NODE ESC "MenuItem ESC-Tabs"

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem ESC-Tabs@{uu}@{ub}


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.

Here you can select, if ESC-Sequencen and Tabs are shown or not.


@{u}ESC-sequences which were rerecognized and executed:@{uu}

 @{b}ESCc@{ub}      Cleared all modes, but no screenclear
 @{b}ESC[0m@{ub}    Cleared all modes
 @{b}ESC[1m@{ub}    Bold on
 @{b}ESC[3m@{ub}    Italic on
 @{b}ESC[4m@{ub}    Underline on
 @{b}ESC[7m@{ub}    Invers on
 @{b}ESC[8m@{ub}    Backgroundcolor for text
 @{b}ESC[22m@{ub}   Bold off
 @{b}ESC[23m@{ub}   Italic off
 @{b}ESC[24m@{ub}   Underline off
 @{b}ESC[27m@{ub}   Invers off
 @{b}ESC[3#m@{ub}   Color (# = 0-7) for text
 @{b}ESC[39m@{ub}   Color 1 for text
 @{b}ESC[4#m@{ub}   Text in front of backgroundcolor (# = 0-7)
 @{b}ESC[49m@{ub}   Text in front of backgroundcolor 0

Kombinations of this sequences were recogniced.
For example: ESC[1;7;37m (bold,invers und Textcolor 7

@{u}ESC-sequences which were rerecognized and deleted:@{uu}

 @{b}ESC[#u@{ub}       Line length #
 @{b}ESC[#t@{ub}       Line number #
 @{b}ESC[#x@{ub}       Pixel spacing # from top
 @{b}ESC[#y@{ub}       Pixel spacing # from left
 @{b}ESC[xx;yyH@{ub}   Cursor in column xx, line yy
 @{b}ESC[J@{ub}        Delete at cursor
 @{b}ESC[@@{ub}        Insert space
 @{b}ESC[#A@{ub}       Cursor # up
 @{b}ESC[#B@{ub}       Cursor # down
 @{b}ESC[#C@{ub}       Cursor # left
 @{b}ESC[#D@{ub}       Cursor # right
 @{b}ESC[#E@{ub}       Cursor # lines down
 @{b}ESC[#F@{ub}       Cursor # lines up
 @{b}ESC[#K@{ub}       to lineend # delete
 @{b}ESC[#L@{ub}       # lines insert
 @{b}ESC[#M@{ub}       # lines delete
 @{b}ESC[#P@{ub}       # chars delete
 @{b}ESC[#S@{ub}       scroll up # lines
 @{b}ESC[#T@{ub}       scroll down # lines

@ENDNODE

@NODE Pub "Menuitem Publicscreen..."

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem Publicscreen...@{uu}@{ub}


Shows a list with all opened publicscreens. You can now select the screen,
on which the MIndicatorwindow will be opened. The windowheight and the
windowwidth depends from the selected, visible screenarea.

@ENDNODE

@NODE GUI "Menuitem Guideindicator..."

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem Guideindicator...@{uu}@{ub}


Opens an ASL-Filerequester in which you can select the indicator for the
.guide-files.

@ENDNODE

@NODE TFo "Menuitem Textfont..."

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem Textfont...@{ub}@{uu}


Opens an ASL-Fontrequester in which you can select the font for the text.
You may not select a proportionalfont.

@ENDNODE

@NODE GFo "Menuitem Gadgetfont..."

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem Gadgetfont...@{ub}@{uu}


Opens an ASL-Fontrequester in which you can select the font for the gadgets.

@ENDNODE

@NODE FOR "Menuitem FormFeed"

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem FormFeed@{ub}@{uu}


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.

Here you can select, if a formfeed is necessery or not.

@ENDNODE

@NODE PRT "Menuitem Print..."

@{b}@{u}The Menuitem Print...@{ub}@{uu}


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.

Opens the Printerwindow, in which you can change printeroptions and start
the printaction.


@{u}Variables for head- and footline:@{uu}

@{b}#f#@{ub} = filename
@{b}#d#@{ub} = printdate
@{b}#t#@{ub} = printtime
@{b}#p#@{ub} = pagenumber


See help for more informations.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Gadgets "Gadgets"

@{b}@{u}The gadgets from MultiIndicator@{ub}@{uu}


MultiIndicator contains the following gadgets:

          Textgadget         @{"Path/Filename" link Text}
          Buttongadget       @{"Search" link Suchen}
          Buttongadget       @{"Next" link Next}
          Buttongadget       @{"Previous" link Prev}
          Slidergadget       @{"Vertical" link Vert}
          Slidergadget       @{"Horizontal" link Horiz}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Text "Textgadget Path/Filename"

@{b}@{u}The Textgadget Path/Filename@{ub}@{uu}


Shows the name of the loaded file. If the name is too long, than the file-
name will be split.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Suchen "Buttongadget Search"

@{b}@{u}The Buttongadget Search@{ub}@{uu}


Opens the Searchwindow, in which you can enter the searchword and change
another options.


See help for more informations.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Next "Buttongadget Next"

@{b}@{u}The Buttongadget Next@{ub}@{uu}


Searches for the next item. If the next item was found, it will be marked.
If no item was found, a window appears which informs you. This Gadget is
selectable if a searchword is inserted.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Prev "Buttongadget Previous"

@{b}@{u}The Buttongadget Previous@{ub}@{uu}


Searches for the previous item. If the previous item was found, it will be
marked. If no item was found, a window appears which informs you. This
Gadget is selectable if a searchword is inserted.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Vert "Slidergadget Vertical"

@{b}@{u}The Slidergadget Vertical@{ub}@{uu}


With this gadget you can scroll the text by the line (arrows), pages (click
below or above the beam) or independent (click in the beam and move). This
works only if the text is longer as one screenpage.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Horiz "Slidergadget Horizontal"

@{b}@{u}The Slidergadget Horizontal@{ub}@{uu}


This Gadget is only available if the selected File is an ASC-File.


With this gadget you can scroll the text by the letter (arrows), pages
(click left or right the beam) or independent (click in the beam and move).
This works only if the text is widen as one screenpage.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Tastatur "Keyboard"

@{b}@{u}Keyboardcontrol@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}@{u}Window:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}ESC:@{ub}                       Mainwindow open -> MultiIndicator terminates
                           Other window open -> window terminates

@{b}@{u}StringGadgets:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Tab:@{ub}                       Next stringgadget activate
@{b}Shift + Tab:@{ub}               Previous stringgadget activate
@{b}Cursor down:@{ub}               Next stringgadget activate
@{b}Cursor up:@{ub}                 Previous stringgadget activate

@{b}@{u}Gadgets allgemein:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Underlined chars:@{ub}          Activate the button or the stringgadget
                           (Only if no stringgadget is activate)

@{b}@{u}Textcontrol:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Cursor up:@{ub}                 Line up
@{b}Cursor down:@{ub}               Line down
@{b}Cursor left:@{ub}               Char left (only ASC-description)
@{b}Cursor right:@{ub}              Char right (only ASC-description)
@{b}Shift + Cursor...:@{ub}         Page...
@{b}Alt + Cursor...:@{ub}           Goto textbegin -end
@{b}Ctrl + Cursor...:@{ub}          Goto textbegin -end

@{u}Numberblock:@{uu}

@{b}Cursor up = 8:@{ub}             Line up
@{b}Cursor down = 2:@{ub}           Line down
@{b}Cursor left = 4:@{ub}           Char left (only ASC-description)
@{b}Cursor right = 6:@{ub}          Char right (only ASC-description)
@{b}Pg Up = 9:@{ub}                 Page up
@{b}Pg Dn = 3:@{ub}                 Page down
@{b}Home = 7:@{ub}                  Goto textbegin
@{b}End = 1:@{ub}                   Goto textend

@ENDNODE

@NODE Sprache "Language"

@{b}@{u}What Language Speaks MultiIndicator@{ub}@{uu}


Have you at least Workbench 2.1, than you can start MultiIndicator in your
language. You must copy the MI.catalog for your language in the directory:

Locale:Catalogs/<language>


@{b}@{u}Appeal:@{ub}@{uu}

I need the @{b}.ct-Files@{ub} for the languages

Danish, Italian, Norwegian, Dutch and Portuguese,

the @{b}.help-Files@{ub} for the languages

Danish, French, Italian, Norwegian, Dutch, Portuguese and Spanish,

the @{b}.guide-Files@{ub} for the languages

Danish, French, Italian, Norwegian, Dutch, Portuguese, Swedish and Spanish,

and the translation of the Install-script.


For the @{b}.ct-File@{ub} the File MI_?.cd is in the directory Catalogs.

If you make a @{b}.help-File@{ub}, the text mustn't be longer than @{u}16 lines@{uu} and
wider than @{u}50 chars@{uu}.

If you make a @{b}.guide-File@{ub}, the text mustn't be wider than @{u}78 chars@{uu}.

@{b}Thanks ahead@{ub}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE XPK "XPK and PowerPacker"

@{b}@{u}The Packer XPK and PowerPacker@{ub}@{uu}


If you want to indicate files, which were compressed by XPK, you need the
XPK.librarys in your directory Libs:.

If you want to indicate files, which were compressed by PowerPacker, you
need the XPKmaster.library and the PowerPacker.library in your directory
Libs:.


XPK were distributed as FD on Fish 754.

PowerPacker is a commercial program.

@ENDNODE

@NODE  Entwicklung "History"

@{b}@{u}The History@{uu}@{ub}


03.08.93  @{b}V0.0@{ub}   Programing begin.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

12.08.93  @{b}V1.0@{ub}   @{b}First public release.@{ub}


----------------------------------------------------------------------------

16.08.93  @{b}V1.1@{ub}   New loadroutine for ASC-text       -> considerable faster

                 New searchroutine for HEX and ASC  -> faster

                 New viewroutine for ASC-text       -> conditional on the
                                                       new loadroutine

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

16.08.93  @{b}V1.11@{ub}  Reworked Shell-parameter handing-over.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

17.08.93  @{b}V1.12@{ub}  ASC-HEX_View can used as DefaultTool.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

18.08.93  @{b}V1.2@{ub}   MultiIndicator opens an AppIcon if you start about Work-
                 bench. Handing-over ToolTypes.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

18.08.93  @{b}V1.21@{ub}  Now you can select in the Searchwindow if the search starts
                 always from the beginning and if the capitalization want to
                 take in account.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

18.08.93  @{b}V1.22@{ub}  Now textcontrol about keyboard.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

19.08.93  @{b}V1.23@{ub}  Name of the program is now MultiIndicator.

                 Keyboardcontrol like CygnusEd implement. (Boris Jakubaschk)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

                 @{b}Second public release.@{ub}

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

21.08.93  @{b}V1.3@{ub}   MultiIndicator can indicate ESC.sequences and Tabs.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

25.08.93  @{b}V1.4@{ub}   XPK-Packer and PowerPacker support.

                 Infowindow available.

                 Buttongadgets changes the look if you selct them.
                 (Boris Jakubaschk)

                 Keyboardcontrol chanced. Alt -> Ctrl. (Boris Jakubaschk)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

30.08.93  @{b}V1.5@{ub}   Printoption for ASC-Texte implement.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

                 @{b}Third public release.@{ub}

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

02.09.93  @{b}V1.5a@{ub}  Spanish Catalog from @{b}José Garcia@{ub}.

                 Catalogs now works under OS3.x.

                 Little Bugs removed.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

09.10.93  @{b}V1.6@{ub}   NewLookMenues under OS3.x.

                 In gadgets you can use proportionalfonts.

                 Window get a zoomgadget.

                 Printwindow reworked.

                 Variables in head- footline allowed.

                 The meaning of formfeed has changed !

                 Checkboxes and MXbuttons skaleable under OS3.x.

                 Graphicsbug in the Pubscreenfenster under OS3.x removed.

                 Searchword will be indicated if it wasn't found.

                 One Enforcerhit removed.

                 Text without lineend in the last line view exactely.

                 More than one packstep allowed.

                 Program can be terminated with ESC-button.

                 Waitpointer changed -> faster

                 If you start the program about AppIcon, it remembers the
                 last path.

                 Help implement.

                 Dynamic stack implement. No stack is necessery, but no
                 control with Mungwall possible.

                 @{"Installer" link Lizenz} implement.

                 @{"AmigaGuide" link Lizenz} implement.

                 Swedish Catalog from @{b}Mikael Silfver@{ub}.

                 New menuitem Open available. (Mikael Silfver)

                 Only the visible area of the screen used. (Jens Bönisch)

                 MI remembers always the last path.

                 @{u}For keyboardfetishists !@{uu}
                 Windows ( without Passwordwindow and ASL-Requester ) can
                 close with ESC.
                 In the Searchwindow you have to press Return twice if the
                 stringgadget is activated and you want to start the search.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

                 @{b}Fourth public release.@{ub}

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

16.11.93  @{b}V1.7@{ub}   Text in the Passwordwindow is invisible.

                 In Stringgadgets you can jump with Cursor up and Cursor
                 down.

                 Program optimized -> c. 22% shorter.

                 A few internal improvements.

                 Now accessible about @{"E-Mail" link Baum}.

                 Swedish Help-File from @{b}Mikael Silfver@{ub}.

                 You can now use the Altkey instead of the Ctrlkey.
                 (Mikael Silfver)

                 Publicscreen can now select with a Doubleclick.
                 (Mikael Silfver)

                 Little Bugs removed. (Mikael Silfver)

                 MI now knows Hex-Code 9b resp. ASC-Code 155. This is the
                 same as 'ESC['. (Would be used in many Mailboxes)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

                 @{b}Fifth public release.@{ub}

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

10.01.94  @{b}V1.7@{ub}   French Catalog from @{b}Pascal Aubert@{ub}.

12.01.94         When the xpk????.librarys will be installed, the
                 Version will be checked.
                 ( Not all !!! Sorry )

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

